"Hymn 1
Saintly voices, ever singing round thy throne of Light
Saintly harps forever ringing, rest not day nor night;
Thousands only live to bless thee, and confess thee, God of Might.
Thou who art beyond the farthest mortal eye can scan,
Could it be that thou regardest songs of sinful man?
Can we feel that thou art near us and wilt hear us? Yes, we can.
Yes, we know that thou rejoicest o'er each work of thine;
Thou didst ears and hands and voices for thy praise design;
Craftsman's art and music's measure for thy pleasure all combine.
Here, great S'Allumer, today we offer of thine own to thee;
And for thine acceptance proffer, all unworthily.
Hearts and minds, and hands and voices, in our choicest melody."

"Hymn 1
Saintly voices, ever singing round thy throne of Light
Saintly harps forever ringing, rest not day nor night;
Thousands only live to bless thee, and confess thee, God of Might.
Thou who art beyond the farthest mortal eye can scan,
Could it be that thou regardest songs of sinful man?
Can we feel that thou art near us and wilt hear us? Yes, we can.
Yes, we know that thou rejoicest o'er each work of thine;
Thou didst ears and hands and voices for thy praise design;
Craftsman's art and music's measure for thy pleasure all combine.
Here, great S'Allumer, today we offer of thine own to thee;
And for thine acceptance proffer, all unworthily.
Hearts and minds, and hands and voices, in our choicest melody."

"Hymn 3
Give to the winds thy fears; hope and be undismayed;
S'allumer hears thy sighs and counts thy tears, S'allumer shall lift thy head.
Through waves and clouds and storms, he gently clears the way;
Wait thou his time; so shall this night soon end in joyous day.
Leave to his sovereign sway to choose and to command;
So shall thou, wondering, own his way, how wise, how strong his hand;
Let us in life, in death, thy steadfast truth declare:
And publish with our latest breath thy love and guardian care."

"Hymn 3
Give to the winds thy fears; hope and be undismayed;
S'allumer hears thy sighs and counts thy tears, S'allumer shall lift thy head.
Through waves and clouds and storms, he gently clears the way;
Wait thou his time; so shall this night soon end in joyous day.
Leave to his sovereign sway to choose and to command;
So shall thou, wondering, own his way, how wise, how strong his hand;
Let us in life, in death, thy steadfast truth declare:
And publish with our latest breath thy love and guardian care."

"Hymn 4
S'allumer is love; his mercy brightens
All the path in which we rove;
Bliss he wakes and woe he lightens;
S'allumer is wisdom, S'allumer is love.
Chance and change are busy ever;
Man decays and ages move;
But his mercy waneth never;
S'allumer is wisdom, S'allumer is love.
E'en the hour that darkest seemeth
Will his changeless goodness prove;
Through the gloom his brightness streameth;
S'allumer is wisdom, S'allumer is love.
He with earthly cares entwineth
Hope and comfort from above;
Everywhere his glory shineth:
S'allumer is wisdom, S'allumer is love."

